<?xml-model href="../schema/schema_cavatina_docbook.rnc" type="application/relax-ng-compact-syntax"?>
<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.1-extended">
    <info>
        <title>Time Signatures</title>
    </info>
    <para>Time signatures have to be written after clefs (and key signatures) or barlines. To start
        a time signature enter the <emphasis role="italic">time</emphasis> key <code>°</code>. After
        that you just write the upper and lower numeral successively. </para>
    <para>To write the <emphasis role="italic">common time</emphasis> or <emphasis role="italic">cut
            time</emphasis> symbols, enter <emphasis role="italic">c</emphasis> or <emphasis
            role="italic">C</emphasis> after the <emphasis role="italic">time</emphasis> key.</para>
    <para>A space is automatically attached after a time signature, so that you don’t have to open a
        new staff block yourself.</para>
    
    <example>
        <title>Example</title>
        <para>
            <informaltable>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Input</entry>
                            <entry>Rendered</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry><code>,°34 ,°1216 ,?'''°34 ,°c ,</code></entry>
                            <entry/>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
        </para>
    </example>
</section>
